NUMBER 2252
NAME Shartan, peaks
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The jagged, snow-covered peaks of Shartan rise towards the clouds mighty
sentinels. Nestled within these peaks, upon a rising plateau, is the
border Keep of Lynieas. The Keep sits upon its craggy ledge, the furthest
outpost of the King's domain. The boulder-strewn terrain rises towards the
plateau to the north, while a small trail leads to a simple cabin to the
east. Somewhere, far to the south, lies the city of Fayd.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT U 2256
ITEM 0 76 ADJ1=294 VAL2=2253
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The rumbling of snow crashing down the peaks can be barely heard above the din caused by the strong mountain wind.
ENDIF
IFVERB RECALL -1
  IFVAR SKILL32 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER Beyond these peaks lies only the undiscovered wastelands of the northern arctic wastelands.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SKILL32 = 2
    ECHO PLAYER Beyond these peaks lies only the undiscovered wastelands of the northern arctic wastelands.
    ECHO PLAYER You realize that these peaks are reputed to be the homeland of the ferocious Mountain Barbarians.
  ENDIF
  IFVAR SKILL32 => 3
    ECHO PLAYER Beyond these peaks lies only the undiscovered wastelands of the northern arctic wastelands.
    ECHO PLAYER You realize that these peaks are reputed to be the homeland of the ferocious Mountain Barbarians.
    ECHO PLAYER The Barony of Lynieas used to be a prominent posting, given to those favored by the King, but no word has come from its Keep in nearly 125 years. Rumors speak of some fell treachery occurring....
  ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2253
NAME Shartan, before cabin
MOUNTAIN
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A simple wooden cabin, constructed from the sturdy trunks of mountain pines,
leans against the side of a sheer cliff wall. A pile of ancient stumps and
branches are leaned up against the outside wall of the cabin's chimney.
Scraggly patches of yellowing grass are chewed upon by a herd of mountain
goats, who ignore your approach. A single wispy plume of smoke rises from
the chimney, giving evidence that someone still uses the place as a home.
The sturdy wooden door that allows entry, seems to be slightly ajar.
A rock-free trail leads back towards the looming presence of Lynieas Keep.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NE 2254
ITEM 0 76 ADJ1=294 VAL2=2252
ITEM 1 66 ADJ1=355 VAL2=2255 OPEN
IFVERB SMELL -1
  ECHO PLAYER The fetid smell of goat is quite strong here.
  ECHO OTHERS %N wrinkles %h nose in distaste while gazing balefully at the sheep.
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER Someone is puttering around inside the cabin, all the while humming a cheery ditty.
ENDIF
;
