NUMBER 2258
NAME Gorge, bottom
MOUNTAIN
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
The sheer sides of the gorge narrow into a small v shape here. The howling
wind is bitterly cold and brings the occasional flake of snow with it as
it blows through the narrow defile. The broken bones strewn around some of
the sharper rocks tells you that more than one being has been careless
at the top of the gorge. The faint remnants of a small trail can be seen
to the west, but the treacherous boulders and snow have, with the passage
of time, blocked that route to safety. The jagged wall with the broken
bridge clattering against it seems to be the only way out of the gorge.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 0 420
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 0
There's enough handholds that you think it would be fairly simple to
climb out of the gorge.
*DESCRIPTION_END
IFENTRY
 IFITEM 2
   ECHO PLAYER There is an opening in the mountain side, leading into a dark tunnel..
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB LISTEN -1
  ECHO PLAYER The rushing of the wind makes it tough to think, much less hear anything...
  ECHO OTHERS %N strains to hear anything above the howling of the wind...
ENDIF
IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
  CLEARVERB
  DISBAND
  RANDOM dummy3 1 100 0
  ADD dummy3 AGI
    IFVAR dummy3 => 210
      ECHO PLAYER You leap up and grab a hold of a protruding rock and then make a short climb to the bottom of the bridge, latching on to that and steadily making your way up the gorge...
      ECHO OTHERS %n leaps up and grabs a hold of a protruding rock and then makes %h way up to the bottom of the swaying bridge, latching on to it and steadily making %h way up the gorge...
      MOVE 2257
      AFFECT 2257
      ECHO OTHERS %N climbs into view.
      AFFECT 2258
      EQUAL ROUNDTIME 20
    ENDIF
      IFVAR dummy3 < 210
        ECHO PLAYER You try and find a handhold to climb up the side of the gorge but fail.
        ECHO OTHERS %N looks futilely along the wall for a place to climb up.
      ENDIF
ENDIF
;
