Khaliban holding a small child lovingly in his arms.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAMINE 6
The beautiful mountain peaks glimmer with a rhapsody of haunting colors
as you gaze through the window at them. Their eternal majesty echoes with
the resonances of times long gone by...
*DESCRIPTION_END
;
NUMBER 2286
NAME Lynieas Keep
DAY_LIGHT
FOREST
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A small verdant grove of trees, which sway softly in the mountain
breezes, surround a spring fed pool whose crystalline waters
glisten like diamonds in the sunlight. A long wooden swing hung
between two of the trees offers a comfortable place to rest. To
the south you see the mighty gates of the keep. A large tower
rises in the east, shadowing the stables nestled in the northern
courtyard. Carved wooden doors lead back into the keep.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT N 2287
EXIT E 2288
EXIT S 2290
ITEM 0 943 ADJ1=46 ADJ2=355 VAL1=500 VAL2=2262 VAL3=4705
ITEM 1 229
ITEM 2 324 ADJ1=112
ITEM 3 1045 ADJ1=183 ADJ2=355
IFPREVERB GO 3
  CLEARVERB
   ECHO PLAYER You sit down on the swing and gently hold on to the ropes that suspend it from the trees.
   ECHO OTHERS %N sits down on the swing and gently takes hold of the ropes that suspend it from the trees.
   EQUAL FLAG1 1
   POSITION SIT
ENDIF
IFPREVERB PUSH 3
  CLEARVERB
   IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
     ECHO PLAYER You push off from the ground with your feet and set the swing in motion, letting it gently carry you back and forth between the beautiful trees that grow in this place.
     ECHO OTHERS %N pushes off from the ground with %h feet, setting the swing in motion...
     ECHO OTHERS %c
     ECHO OTHERS %N swings back and forth amidst the profusion of beautiful trees and bushes.
   ENDIF
    IFVAR FLAG1 ! 1
      ECHO PLAYER You gently push the swing back and forth.
      ECHO OTHERS %N gently pushes the swing back and forth.
    ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB STAND -1
  IFVAR FLAG1 = 1
    ECHO PLAYER You get off the swing.
    ECHO OTHERS %N gets off the swing.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2287
NAME Lynieas Keep, stables
FIXED_LIGHT
INDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A mound of hay lies against the back wall of the stable here. On
the eastern and western sides of the stable you see rows of
stalls. Near the side of each stall, saddles and bridles hang
from wooden pegs. You also see pitchforks and several kinds of
tools attached to a rack on the eastern wall. In the middle of
the room you see two troughs one which holds water and another
which holds grain. A ladder leads up into a hayloft.
*DESCRIPTION_END
