NAME Lynieas Keep, barracks
DAY_LIGHT
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
A large stone building lies here against the eastern wall. This
is the barracks for the standing guard of Lynieas keep. Mossy
green lichen clings to the building in an unusual spiral
formation. A flat patch of fertile land here is used as a small
garden for the keep. You see a granite stairway which leads up
onto the stone fortifications and battlements. Heavy wooden double
doors lead inside.
*DESCRIPTION_END
