ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
You stand upon the fortifications which guard the western sides
of the keep. Stacks of spears and supplies for archers sit under
tarps toprotect them against the rain and snow so common in this
northern land. A short distance to the west, a huge moutain
leaves you feeling insignificant in the greater scheme of things.
A narrow crossway goes to the southern ramparts, a stone stairway
leads back down to the courtyard.
*DESCRIPTION_END
