NUMBER 2299
NAME Southern Fortifications
OUTDOOR_FLOOR
DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ITEM 9 693
*DESCRIPTION_START
These battlements are the most lightly guarded of the four walls.
To the south of the keep, a huge gorge makes an attack from this
direction unlikely. Glancing below you see a rock pathway which
leads from the mighty iron gates down to the small bridge which
crosses the gorge. A narrow crossway goes back to the western
fortifications.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT NW 2298
